      • setIndex

        public void setIndex(int i)
        Sets the index of a body, used to select a minor body when reading asteroids/comets. Default initial value for index is -1.
        Parameters:

      • getIndex

        public int getIndex()
        Returns the index, or -1 if it is not set.
        Returns:
        The index.

      • isValidObjectButNotASatelliteNeitherAnAsteroid

        public boolean isValidObjectButNotASatelliteNeitherAnAsteroid()
        Check if the index is indeed a valid index of an object. The check is made for main objects suitable for ephemeris calculations, such as the Sun, the Moon, any planet except Earth, and Pluto. If the index is a valid one but is not an index of a given asteroid or a natural satellite (neither the Earth or its barycenter), true will be returned. If the index is equal to a generic Comet/Asteroid true will be returned since this is valid for that specific kind of calculations.
        Returns:
        True if it is a valid index, false otherwise.

      • isNaturalSatellite

        public boolean isNaturalSatellite()
        Check if the index is indeed a valid index of a natural satellite.
        Returns:
        True if it is a valid satellite, false otherwise. Note this method returns false for the Moon.

      • isPlanet

        public boolean isPlanet()
        Check if the index is indeed a planet.
        Returns:
        True if it is a planet or the Sun, false otherwise.

      • isAsteroid

        public boolean isAsteroid()
        Check if the index is indeed an asteroid (or comet).
        Returns:
        True if it is an asteroid, false otherwise.

        public double getFlatenningFactor()
